# AI Chatbot — Frontend Cursor Rules (Day 1)

## What we are building today
1. Login page
2. Register page
3. Protected chat route
4. Chat page (message bubbles + input + loading state)
5. API calls (mocked for now — real backend connects tomorrow)

---

## Tech Stack (Frontend Only Today)
- Next.js 16 — App Router only, no Pages Router
- React 19
- Tailwind CSS 4
- TypeScript (strict mode)
- NO external component libraries — build everything with Tailwind

---

## Folder Structure

```
frontend/
├── app/
│   ├── layout.tsx              # Root layout
│   ├── page.tsx                # Redirects to /login
│   ├── globals.css             # Tailwind 4 import
│   ├── (auth)/
│   │   ├── login/
│   │   │   └── page.tsx        # Login page
│   │   └── register/
│   │       └── page.tsx        # Register page
│   └── chat/
│       └── page.tsx            # Chat page (protected)
├── components/
│   ├── auth/
│   │   ├── LoginForm.tsx       # Login form component
│   │   └── RegisterForm.tsx    # Register form component
│   └── chat/
│       ├── ChatWindow.tsx      # Scrollable message list
│       ├── MessageBubble.tsx   # Single message (user or AI)
│       └── MessageInput.tsx    # Text input + send button
├── lib/
│   ├── auth.ts                 # login(), register(), logout(), getToken()
│   └── api.ts                  # sendMessage(), getMessages() — mocked today
├── hooks/
│   └── useAuth.ts              # useAuth hook — reads token, redirects if missing
├── types/
│   └── index.ts                # All TypeScript types
└── middleware.ts               # Route protection (redirects /chat to /login)
```

