## Component Rules

### MessageBubble.tsx
- User messages: aligned right, colored background (e.g. blue/indigo)
- AI messages: aligned left, neutral background (gray)
- Show sender label above each bubble ("You" or "AI")
- No avatars needed today

### ChatWindow.tsx
- Scrollable container — use `overflow-y-auto` with a fixed height
- Auto-scroll to bottom when new message arrives — use `useEffect` + `useRef`
- Show a centered loading spinner when AI is thinking
- Map over messages array and render `<MessageBubble />` for each

### MessageInput.tsx
- Textarea (not input) so user can type long messages
- Send button on the right
- Disable both textarea and button while AI is loading
- Submit on button click OR Ctrl+Enter keyboard shortcut
- Clear input after sending
- Show character count — warn if over 1000 chars

### LoginForm.tsx / RegisterForm.tsx
- Controlled inputs with `useState`
- Show inline error message below each field
- Show a general error (e.g. "Invalid credentials") above the submit button
- Disable the submit button while loading
- Show a spinner inside the button while loading
- After successful login → `router.push('/chat')`

---

## UI Design Rules

- Keep it simple and clean — this is not a portfolio piece today, it's a working prototype
- Color scheme: white background, indigo/blue for primary actions, gray for secondary
- User message bubble: `bg-indigo-600 text-white` aligned right
- AI message bubble: `bg-gray-100 text-gray-800` aligned left
- Font: default Tailwind sans — no custom fonts today
- Spacing: generous padding on all containers — `p-4` or `p-6`
- No animations or transitions today — add later
- Mobile layout is not a priority today — desktop first

---

## Error Handling Rules

- Every async function must have try/catch
- Show errors to the user — never silently swallow them
- If Gemini (mocked) fails — show "Something went wrong. Please try again." in the chat
- If login fails — show the error message from the thrown Error
- Console.error is okay during development — remove before production

---

## What NOT to build today

- Do NOT build a sessions sidebar — one session per user is enough
- Do NOT add markdown rendering for AI responses — plain text only
- Do NOT add file uploads
- Do NOT add dark mode toggle — focus on core functionality
- Do NOT spend time on animations
- Do NOT build a user settings or profile page
- Do NOT implement token refresh logic — single access token is fine today

